        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2457993118" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4392997171219368093">Wonderfully evocative of the flora and fauna of Grand Canyon, Brighty&apos;s tale also captures the wildness, danger, and beauty of the years leading up to the establishment of the national park. I&apos;m not sure how Marguerite Henry did it, but as with Justin Morgan and King of the Wind, she managed to give the animal&apos;s point of view without anthropomorphizing him.<br/><br/>Last night I went and applied for the lottery to stay at Phantom Ranch at the bottom of the canyon.</span>
  <span id="freeText4392997171219368093" style="display:none">Wonderfully evocative of the flora and fauna of Grand Canyon, Brighty's tale also captures the wildness, danger, and beauty of the years leading up to the establishment of the national park. I'm not sure how Marguerite Henry did it, but as with Justin Morgan and King of the Wind, she managed to give the animal's point of view without anthropomorphizing him.<br /><br />Last night I went and applied for the lottery to stay at Phantom Ranch at the bottom of the canyon.</span>
